Both of these two books represent historical narratives of the philosophical tradition in the West, the main difference being that &quot;The Dream of Reason&quot; focuses more on the actual history as such, while &quot;The Cave and the Light&quot; focuses more on the recurring themes and ideas that have manifested themselves throughout this history
